      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 2004 BMW M3, a definitive example of the E46 chassis. This specimen features the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies and a precise 6-speed manual transmission. The engine exhibits flawless VANOS operation and has undergone a recent valve adjustment to factory specifications. Mechanically, the vehicle is superlative; the rear subframe has been proactively reinforced with Turner Motorsport plates, and the suspension retains its factory-spec damping with refreshed bushings throughout. The Variable M Differential Lock provides optimal torque distribution, and the braking system utilizes cross-drilled rotors with zero pulsation. The exterior factory finish displays consistent depth across all panels, and the interior Nappa leather bolsters show no signs of compression or wear. A true turn-key investment for the discerning collector.",
